# WebGPU / Three.js dev tooling

New sketches and demos use the shared dev HUD in `src/lib/devTools.ts`.

## Required layout

| Concern | Location |
|---------|----------|
| Param defaults + Tweakpane ranges | `*params.ts` next to the demo (see `devTools.params.example.ts`) |
| WGSL | `src/shaders/<name>.wgsl` — import with `?raw` |
| Dev HUD wiring | `createDevTools()` in demo entry |

## Param schema (single source of truth)

Define defaults and pane metadata together. Bump `SCHEMA_VERSION` when folders/keys change — localStorage is discarded on mismatch (no migration of old schemas).

```ts
export const SCHEMA_VERSION = "my-demo-v2";
export const PARAM_SCHEMA = {
  particles: { count: { value: 65536, min: 1024, max: 1e6, step: 1024 } },
  debug: { landmarks: { value: false, label: "landmark overlays" } },
} satisfies ParamSchema;
```

## Dev HUD behavior

- **/** toggles **both** fps/ms stats and Tweakpane together (visible by default)
- **.** resets all params to code defaults and clears stored values
- **m** toggles `debug.landmarks` (also in Debug folder)
- Params persist in `localStorage` keyed by `storageKey` + `schemaVersion`

## WGSL

Never inline large shader strings in `.ts` files. Keep `.wgsl` files separate for editor highlighting:

```ts
import simShader from "../shaders/sim.wgsl?raw";
```

## Wiring snippet

```ts
import { createDevTools } from "../lib/devTools";
import { PARAM_SCHEMA, SCHEMA_VERSION } from "./myDemo.params";

const dev = createDevTools({
  schema: PARAM_SCHEMA,
  schemaVersion: SCHEMA_VERSION,
  storageKey: "my-demo-params",
  onChange: (p) => applyUniforms(p),
  onLandmarksChange: (on) => landmarkLayer.visible = on,
});

// each frame:
dev.tick();
```

Dependencies: `tweakpane`, `stats.js`.
